						               													<description>&amp;#233;&amp;#173;&amp;#148;&amp;#231;&amp;#142;&amp;#139;&amp;#229;&amp;#164;&amp;#167;&amp;#230;&amp;#136;&amp;#166;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#150;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#131;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#136;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#144;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#175;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#169;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#131;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#183;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#165; (Satans War Buttoba Crash) is an action game from Japan. Players flick their monsters onto Satan's castle, trying to earn enough reward to gather three 'heroes'. The first player to recruit three heroes, such as Dracula, Succubus, Vorpal Bunny, or Hanako in the toilet, is the winner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;One player acts as Satan and defends a large castle, made from staggered boxes as a dias, with a throne at the top. The other players have a Demon King, one of eight such as Lucifer, Cthulhu, or Nurarihyon. Each Demon King starts with special abilities to help the player.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game uses highly decorated plastic cards. The player takes their plastic Demon King card and inserts it vertical into a base card. This creates a flicking device. By holding the base down, and bending the card back, a player can flick their small foam creatures up onto the castle levels. Satan can defend the castle platform with its own cards, or use whatever toys or plushies a player has to hand.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;As the game progresses, the attackers try to steal money from the castle, and use this to recruit 'heroes' to their side. These heroes bring more powers and abilities to the cause, and strengthen the attack in different ways. For example, the Vorpal Bunny increases the attack magnification to the throne by 100 times and exerts super high firepower, but Hanako in the toilet nullifies the attack on the throne. Getting Hanako-san from the toilet keeps the player with Vorpal Bunny in check. Players can choose to work together, and a player might even be better off attacking themselves. The game system is very open and fluid in the way the characters' abilities work.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The first player to gain three heroes to their side is the winner.&amp;#10;user summary&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
